Defendant Mylah Sharmice Hatchett in court with attorney Victoria M McCandless.  Defendant Mylah Sharmice Hatchett in custody.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds. Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements by the State, defense counsel and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Court ordered defendant to serve 12 months at the House of Correction, as follows:
4 months straight time; no release; 8 months to be with release to  the CJRC program.  

While serving sentence, Court ordered defendant to remain compliant with the CJRC program and do the following:
 - Remain controlled substance and alcohol free;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with the Sunglass Hut at Mayfair Mall, city of Wauwatosa, county of Milwaukee, Wisconsin; 
 - No contact with Rydear D.;
 - Parenting classes/course;
 - Obtain GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling.

Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample, if one has not been previously provided, and pay the DNA surcharge, all costs and disbursements within 18 months of today's date (by 11/09/15).  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Court set restitution at zero.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment.
